summary: travelskitty vol. 11 - glasgow pt 1!  we were lucky enough to get a clear day for our first day in the city! after a slightly...
caption:
travelskitty vol. 11 - glasgow pt 1!

we were lucky enough to get a clear day for our first day in the city! after a slightly terrifying encounter with a store selling pokemon merch (it’s hard to explain why they’re all in bags) we were able to reach our hotel in the west end. they were nice enough to upgrade our room while keeping the wonderful value, from where we got some gorgeous photos through the windowsill! i absolutely adore the architecture throughout glasgow and we really got a great view with the sunshine.

one of those generic white cups that came with the tea set provided travelskitty with a comfortable seat to watch the sun go down in the evening. as a photographer and an individual i’m excited for the lengthening days as the year passes on.

until next time,

goodbye from travelskitty!

summary: Now would you look at that. Vegeta Koga made it into the Elite Four. And he stepped up his game and decided that, no, he isn't a...
body:
Now would you look at that. Vegeta Koga made it into the Elite Four. And he stepped up his game and decided that, no, he isn’t a poison master anymore, he is a ninja. Scary. But he at least tried to get tactical. Not his fault that most of his Pokémon were vulnerable to my chosen type. Forretress was supposed to be hard, but my Kadabra also knew Fire Punch, so…

Here he tells me, that he has lost and I may continue my league experience. Or something like that. Anyway, that’s number two of the Elite Four down. Yay me.

This is me if I were a pokemon:
Briiopuu
A fairy/grass type, it’s wood body and moss coverings are unique to each pokemon as...
body:
This is me if I were a pokemon:

Briiopuu

A fairy/grass type, it’s wood body and moss coverings are unique to each pokemon as well as to the region it was born. Briiopuu are sweet, loyal, slow, and often kept as pets. They love dampness, sunshine, and being carried.

When heavily, heavily provoked, they open their eyes and release an acidic mist that disentegrates pretty much anything in its path.

Granchu

Granbull and Raichu fusion

Electric/Fairy Type

Ability: Static/Intimidate

Hidden Ability: Paralysing Punch - Punching moves have a 25% chance to paralyse the opponent.

Stats: HP - 75, Atk - 125, Def - 65, SpA - 85, SpD - 80, Spe - 105

The Courageous Pokemon

Granchu is timid but will stand up for its beliefs if threatened.  Its jaws act as rods and static sometimes shoots between them. It mainly uses its fists to fight but its jaws can do major damage.

summary: Turns out this whole time my friend thought I was joking when I called my Victreebel adorable. I kept shoving my phone in his...
body:
Turns out this whole time my friend thought I was joking when I called my Victreebel adorable. I kept shoving my phone in his face to show him pictures and gush over her, and he assumed I was just jokingly calling it my precious sweetheart because of that one battle it won me.

Like no, I’m 100% serious. I think Victreebel (as well as the rest of its evo line) is the cutest, most perfect creature in all known universes. Completely unironically. This is my favorite Pokémon and I would do anything for it. And yes he still needs to look at every single photo.

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.
